{"summary":"Added session mode option to run code in baseline mode for benchmark comparisons.","project":{"language":"Python"},"files":[{"path":"scripts/elephant_cli.py","content":"# Add session mode option

# In the existing elephant_cli.py, add a new command for session mode
# that allows running code in baseline mode for benchmark comparisons.

import argparse

# Define the new session command

def run_session_mode(args):
    # Logic to run code in baseline mode
    print("Running in baseline mode...")

# Update the command list to include session
COMMANDS = ("plan", "code", "agents", "persona", "plugins", "git", "stats", "test", "session")

# Update the argument parser to handle the new session command

def _build_parser():
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description="Elephant Coder CLI")
    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest='command')
    for command in COMMANDS:
        subparser = subparsers.add_parser(command)
        if command == "session":
            subparser.set_defaults(func=run_session_mode)
    return parser
